snippet.title: Barron Trump & Princess Leonor's Honeymoon In The Bahamas | Crown & Coastline Sung By Barron Trump
snippet.description:
Crown & Coastline

Check us out on Spotify! https://open.spotify.com/album/3y1CZVxPBVqYl2ljdNVWno?si=lLRWLYbeQcuXD9TQDeKi7A

⬇️⬇️⬇️ Watch more videos below! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
https://youtu.be/WBHJZs8ZeFQ
https://youtu.be/GAdihLnAiXk
https://youtu.be/SZZW8YMZlMg?si=kP7ZE5s5fhhjjpX2
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hq_JjAodbY0

Lyrics:

(Verse 1)
I used to walk through marble halls alone,
A quiet prince without a throne.
Then you appeared, a spark, a sign —
A royal light that matched with mine.

You smiled in silk, the world stood still,
Madrid to D.C., hearts to fill.
We danced through doubt, we broke the mold,
Now here we are, our story told.

(Pre-Chorus)
Forget the flash, the flashing lights,
It’s just your hand in mine tonight.

(Chorus)
Now we’re sailing past the world we knew,
Just me and you, in skies so blue.
From palace gold to ocean views,
A king and queen with nothing to prove.
The waves may crash, the tides may turn,
But our love’s the fire that always burns.
Princess to queen, I’m by your side —
My heart, your throne, our royal ride.

(Verse 2)
Sunsets in Nassau, barefoot walks,
We traded guards for quiet talks.
No press, no pressure, just the breeze,
Whispers of vows beneath palm trees.

We built a kingdom in the sand,
No court, no crown — just holding hands.
You laughed and said, “This feels so right,”
And kissed me under Bahama night.

(Pre-Chorus)
Let the world keep watching close,
They’ll never know what we know most.

(Chorus)
Now we’re sailing past the world we knew,
Just me and you, in skies so blue.
From palace gold to ocean views,
A king and queen with nothing to prove.
The waves may crash, the tides may turn,
But our love’s the fire that always burns.
Princess to queen, I’m by your side —
My heart, your throne, our royal ride.

(Bridge)
We'll write a future they can't predict,
A love too strong for politics.
You're not just royal — you're my muse,
My crown, my calm, my every truth.

(Final Chorus)
Now we’re sailing past the world we knew,
With every breath, I vow to you:
No matter storms or royal views,
I’ll build each kingdom just for two.
The stars will rise, and time may fly,
But we’re forever — you and I.
Princess to queen, you're now my bride —
And love’s the law we’ll live inside.

(Outro)
Yeah, love’s the law — and you’re my pride.
From crown to coastline, you're my bride.
